The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 29 October is 5,524 (639.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 24 October, there were 705 new confirmed cases (81.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 17 October, there were 420 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 68% ( 285 extra cases).
